question: In which nation "Topes de Collantes" nature reserve park is located?
explanation: Topes de Collantes nature reserve park is located in the Escambray Mountains of Cuba. This nature reserve park houses the third highest peak in Cuba. It lies along the Potrerillo Peak and San Juan Peak. It houses two UNESCO World Heritage Sites- Valle de Los Ingenios (Valley of the Sugar Mills) and Trinidad city which clearly manifests the wealthy colonial Cuba of the early 17th century.
